@{b}WHEN@{ub}

Usage:@{b}WHEN expression [THEN [;] [conditional statement]]@{ub}

The WHEN instruction is similar to the @{"IF" LINK "IF/main"} instruction, but is valid only within
a @{"SELECT" LINK "SELECT/main"} range. Each WHEN expression is evaluated in turn and must result in a
boolean value. If the result is a 1, the conditional statement is executed and
control passes to the @{"END" LINK "END/main"} statement that terminates the SELECT. As in the case
of the IF instruction, the THEN need not be part of the same clause.

Example:
@{fg shine}
        select;

            when (i < j) then say 'less'

            when (i = j) then say 'equal'

            otherwise say 'greater'
        end
@{fg text}
@ENDNODE
